Package com.smartsheet.api.internal

Class AbstractResources

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.smartsheet.api.internal.AbstractResources
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractAssociatedResources, AttachmentResourcesImpl, AttachmentVersioningResourcesImpl, CommentAttachmentResourcesImpl, CommentResourcesImpl, ContactResourcesImpl, DiscussionAttachmentResourcesImpl, DiscussionCommentResourcesImpl, DiscussionResourcesImpl, EventResourcesImpl, FavoriteResourcesImpl, FolderResourcesImpl, GroupResourcesImpl, HomeFolderResourcesImpl, HomeResourcesImpl, ImageUrlResourcesImpl, PassthroughResourcesImpl, ReportResourcesImpl, RowAttachmentResourcesImpl, RowColumnResourcesImpl, RowDiscussionResourcesImpl, SearchResourcesImpl, ServerInfoResourcesImpl, SheetAttachmentResourcesImpl, SheetAutomationRuleResourcesImpl, SheetColumnResourcesImpl, SheetCommentResourcesImpl, SheetCrossSheetReferenceResourcesImpl, SheetDiscussionResourcesImpl, SheetFilterResourcesImpl, SheetResourcesImpl, SheetRowResourcesImpl, SheetSummaryResourcesImpl, SheetUpdateRequestResourcesImpl, SightResourcesImpl, TemplateResourcesImpl, TokenResourcesImpl, UserResourcesImpl, WebhookResourcesImpl, WorkspaceFolderResourcesImpl, WorkspaceResourcesImpl
    public abstract class AbstractResources
extends java.lang.Object
    This is the base class of the Smartsheet REST API resources. Thread Safety: This class is thread safe because it is immutable and the underlying SmartsheetImpl is thread safe.

      • getResource

        protected <T> T getResource​(java.lang.String path,
                            java.lang.Class<T> objectClass)
                     throws SmartsheetException
        Get a resource from Smartsheet REST API. Parameters: - path : the relative path of the resource - objectClass : the resource object class Returns: the resource (note that if there is no such resource, this method will throw ResourceNotFoundException rather than returning null). Exceptions: - InvalidRequestException : if there is any problem with the REST API request AuthorizationException : if there is any problem with the REST API authorization(access token) ResourceNotFoundException : if the resource can not be found ServiceUnavailableException : if the REST API service is not available (possibly due to rate limiting) SmartsheetRestException : if there is any other REST API related error occurred during the operation SmartsheetException : if there is any other error occurred during the operation
        Type Parameters:
        T - the generic type
        Parameters:
        path - the relative path of the resource.
        objectClass - the object class
        Returns:
        the resource
        Throws:
        SmartsheetException - the smartsheet exception
